
[1]hypocaust

   HYP'OCAUST, n. [Gr. to burn.]

   1. Among the Greeks and Romans, a subterraneous place where was a
   furnace to heat baths.

   2. Among the moderns,the place where a fire is kept to warm a stove or
   a hot-house.
